  <thing id="fMPNMPAlly" name="Ally" description="{b}Benefit{/b}: Choose one Ordinary archetype for your ally to be. That ally should be defined by the DM at a level equal to the hero at the time the feat is taken, but will not gain levels. The ally will assist the hero in any way possible, up to and including dying for the hero. This feat may be taken multiple times. \n\nEach time it is taken, it can either represent a new ally or a level increase to an existing ally. For each level increase taken, increase the ally&apos;s level closer to that of the hero" compset="Feat" summary="You know someone who will always come to your aid.">
