  <thing id="cMPNMPWnSm" name="Winning Smile" description="An entertainer develops such a force of personal magnetism that he can convince a single target to regard him as a trusted friend. The target makes a Will saving throw to avoid being persuaded by the entertainer&apos;s words and actions. The DC is 10 + 1/2 class level + Charisma bonus and Fame score.\n\nThis ability doesn&apos;t enable the entertainer to control the target, but the target perceives the entertainer&apos;s words and actions in the most favorable way. The entertainer can try to give the target orders, but he or she must win an opposed Charisma check to convince the target to perform any actions the target wouldn&apos;t normally undertake. The target never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders, and any act by the entertainer or his allies that threatens the target breaks the mood and clears the target&apos;s head. Otherwise, a target remains won over for 1 minute per level.\n\nAfter the duration expires, the GM determines the reaction and attitude of the target based on what the entertainer compelled the target to do." compset="CustomSpec" summary="You manage to talk others into doing things they would not normally do." uniqueness="unique">
